  <title translate="true">segment attributes</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Segments</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> are hierarchical names, similar to directory or folder pathnames, given to vectors and other data objects (notes and flags) via the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SEG_Directives" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">#Segment Directive</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;By assigning attributes to segment tree</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">branches you can control the visibility, styles, and colors of map features.</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The segment tree is accessible from the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Segment_Page" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Segments Page</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> of the review dialog.</text></para>
  </body>
